Actually `"hello".lastIndexOf("")` returns 5 (the length), which is NOT -1, so the `if` condition is false and we DON'T return early. The data processing continues. This means the mutation actually removes the optimization guard, potentially processing chunks that don't have newlines yet, which could cause issues with partial rows.

The original skips processing when no newline is present (optimization). The mutation always processes. This could cause issues when a chunk ends mid-row.

